1. Meta shareholders have voted down the proposal to include Bitcoin in the reserve;
2. The LOUD issuance whitelist check tool has been launched;
3. The previous reverse copy James Wynn address is currently doing long with James Wynn, and the current position has a floating loss of US$3.38 million;
4. WLFI: USD1 will be the only designated stablecoin for Sahara Labs' issuance activities;
5. Revolving Games completed a new round of financing led by Pantera Capital;
6. The US spot Bitcoin ETF had a net outflow of US$614.02 million yesterday, the largest single-day outflow since February 26;
7. The US Ethereum spot ETF had a net inflow of US$70.2402 million yesterday, continuing a net inflow for 10 days.
